+++++# Objective
+++++
+++++Minimize val_bpb (validation bits per byte) for a fixed 5-minute single-GPU training run.
+++++
+++++# Hypothesis
+++++
+++++**Replace ReLU-squared with SwiGLU in MLP**
+++++
+++++Rationale: SwiGLU (gated SiLU) consistently outperforms ReLU² in transformer language models across scales (Shazeer 2020, LLaMA). The gating mechanism provides smoother gradients and better feature selection. At equal FLOPs the improvement is typically 1-3% in loss. While this adds a gate projection, the inner dimension can be adjusted to keep param count similar.
+++++
+++++# Planned changes
+++++
+++++In train.py MLP class: add a gate linear c_gate = nn.Linear(n_embd, 4*n_embd, bias=False). In forward(), compute gate = F.silu(self.c_gate(x)) and up = self.c_fc(x), then x = gate * up before c_proj. Update init_weights to initialize c_gate with the same uniform distribution as c_fc. The 4x inner dim is kept (slight param increase) for simplicity; reducing to 8/3*n_embd is an optional follow-up.
+++++
+++++# Rules
+++++
+++++1. **Only modify files matching these patterns — touch nothing else:**
+++++- You may modify `train.py` to optimize for val_bpb.
+++++
